Don't take:
Calcium without appropriate co-factors vitamin D3 and K2;
Vitamin A (retinol or retinol palmitate);
Iron (ask GP for a serum ferritin test and transferrin saturation) check your multivitamin get one for seniors without iron;
Vitamin B6 (check multivitamins). Even 50mg per day for seniors can be too much. 1.5mg for women and 1.7mg for men daily. More than 5-10mg daily is unnecessary.

Take:
Magnesium (not magnesium oxide) glycinate, citrate or malate 250-400mg daily;
Vitamin D3 cholecalciferol 1,000-2,000 iu daily;
Vitamin B12 (methylcobalamin or cyanocobalamin) 500-1,000mg daily;
Omega 3 fatty acids (EPA and DHA) at least 1,000mg daily (2,000mg for those with heart issues under doctor guidance);
